STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251029T212436Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260211T161523Z
DESCRIPTION:Ryan Decker\, Associate Professor of Economics\; Director for t
 he Center for Financial Literacy\; North Central College\, breaks down the
  basics of personal finance: budgeting and introductory saving and investm
 ent strategies. Learn which factors to consider for deciding when\, where\
 , and how to save\, invest\, or aggressively tackle debt. Resources and to
 ols for learning more about these topics will be shared.This is one of a c
 ollaborative series of virtual events presented by BIG (Business Interest 
 Group) and co-sponsored by 23 public libraries in the Chicago area for Fin
 ancial Fitness 2026.Register for this webinar here:https://us02web.zoom.us
 /webinar/register/WN_5oXcK8R7S0OoV97Z4VJ2FA
