BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:36666
DTSTAMP:20260314T214529Z
SUMMARY:1917 on the Homefront: How American Families Faced The War to End A
 ll Wars
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.wnpld.org/event/1917-homefront-how-american-famil
 ies-faced-war-end-all-wars-36666
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251125T002141Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260211T161555Z
DESCRIPTION:A reluctant but energetic America entered the fighting in 1917.
  We sent our sons. We rationed our bread. We stopped wearing corsets to sa
 ve the steel for warships… and we wrote and sang the songs that rallied 
 the troops.  Ellie from ElliePresents will transport the audience there w
 ith the sights\, sounds and tastes of the era.
CATEGORIES:Live Performance
DTSTART:20260425T190000Z
DTEND:20260425T200000Z
LOCATION:1785 Orchard Lane\, Northfield\, IL\, 60093\, US
ROOM:Northfield Community Room
GEO:42.100636;-87.770492
END:VEVENT
