BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:37099
DTSTAMP:20260314T214529Z
SUMMARY:America's Oddest Museums - Film Screening
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.wnpld.org/event/americas-oddest-museums-37099
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251203T224205Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260211T161605Z
DESCRIPTION:Join multi-Emmy Award winning producer and editor Harvey Moshma
 n for a screening of a 1-hour special of the PBS series Wild Travels. When
  it comes to museums\, there’s the kind your school made you go to on fi
 eld trips\, but what about the quirkier variety that feature collections o
 f mustard\, or pinball machines\, or even just dust\; that showcase action
  figures\, or portraits made entirely from bugs? The kind of museums that 
 are located in motel lobbies\, or in homemade castles\, or abandoned barns
 ? Learn about them all in AMERICA'S ODDEST MUSEUMS. Screening followed by 
 live Q&A.
CATEGORIES:History,Other
DTSTART:20260503T190000Z
DTEND:20260503T203000Z
LOCATION:768 Oak Street\, Winnetka\, IL\, 60093\, US
ROOM:Lloyd Room
GEO:42.1043086;-87.732896
